# Ditto Synthetic Matchmaking Feedback Loop Simulator — Implementation Plan

## Goal

Implement the core system described in [Synthetic_Conversation_Generator_Project_Roadmap.md](file:///c:/Onedrive/OneDrive%20-%20University%20of%20Southern%20California/Desktop/Job%20Hunting/Ditto-Synthetic-Matchmaking-Feedback-Loop-Simulator/doc/Synthetic_Conversation_Generator_Project_Roadmap.md): a multi-agent simulator that generates synthetic matchmaking conversations between a Ditto-style bot and persona-driven user bots, producing structured JSONL logs for future feedback analysis.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **LLM Provider Choice**: The roadmap lists Claude, Gemini, GPT, and local models. The existing codebase uses **Gemini 2.5 Flash** via `google-genai`. I'll use Gemini as the primary provider (your API key is already configured) and build an abstraction layer so other providers can be swapped in later. For embedding-based similarity scoring, I'll use Gemini's embedding model. Is this acceptable, or do you want multi-provider support from day one?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Multi-Agent Framework**: The roadmap suggests LangGraph/CrewAI. I'll implement a **lightweight custom orchestrator** using pure Python (async) rather than adding a heavy framework dependency — this keeps the codebase simple, portable, and interview-demonstrable. The architecture will be compatible with LangGraph migration later. Agree?

> [!WARNING]
> **Local Model Support / Cost Optimization**: For generating 300–500 conversations (each with multiple LLM calls), API costs could be significant. I'll add a configurable `--dry-run` mode and a `--num-conversations` flag so you can test with small batches first. Full 500-conversation generation can be done when ready.

---

